results.name: Number of divisors d of number n such that d does not divide sigma(n).
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..20000
example: For n = 12, a(12) = 3; sigma(12) = 28, divisors of 12: 1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 12; d does not divide sigma(n) for 3 divisors d: 3, 6 and 12.
mathematica: Table[DivisorSum[n, 1 &, ! Divisible[DivisorSigma[1, n], #] &], {n, 98}] (* _Michael De Vlieger_, Oct 08 2017 *)
